bug.short_desc: Plugging in external USB keyboard immediatly crashes Fedora
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1235951 Keyboard Log
Description of problem:
Whenever I plug in a keyboard into my laptop Fedora immediately crashes / freezes and the GUI breaks. If I boot with the keyboard plugged in before the computer is turned on, it works, and unplugging it does not crash Fedora, but plugging it back in does. I've uploaded the journalctl logs to see if someone can find whats going on. With the keyboard.
The exact same issue happens with USB flash drives, but it works when it's plugged in the first time when the computer has already booted. But if unplugged than plugged back in again Fedora crashes.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
4.8.15
How reproducible:
Most likely hardware dependent.
Running Intel Core i7 Kaby Lake-7500U
Intel HD 620 Graphics
Steps to Reproduce: 1. 2. 3.
Actual results:
Fedora crashes
Expected results:
Should be able to unplug and plug in usb devices without issues.
Additional info:
The USB flash drive seems to not be an issue, only plugging in a USB keyboard.

*********** MASS BUG UPDATE ************** We apologize for the inconvenience. There is a large number of bugs to go through and several of them have gone stale. Due to this, we are doing a mass bug update across all of the Fedora 25 kernel bugs.
Fedora 25 has now been rebased to 4.9.3-200.fc25. Please test this kernel update (or newer) and let us know if you issue has been resolved or if it is still present with the newer kernel.
If you have moved on to Fedora 26, and are still experiencing this issue, please change the version to Fedora 26.
If you experience different issues, please open a new bug report for those.
Thanks for letting us know. I'm going to close the bug, please reopen if the problem shows up again.
